parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall repair can lead to a delay in fixing the potentially faulty airbag system, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the unavailability of parts for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in the event of an accident
resulting in injuries to the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end wobble, also known as the "death wobble," can cause the vehicle to become unstable and difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's front end shakes or wobbles violently

often when driving at high speeds (above 50 mph) and hitting bumps or rough road surfaces. The wobble can be so severe that it affects steering control and causes the vehicle to drift or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to become unstable and difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to bottom out erratically
or experience a severe wobble or shake.
